The paper focuses on designing a teleoperation algorithm for assistive robots, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The algorithm involves learning latent actions, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the usability of the algorithm through user studies, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper mentions formulating properties that the latent actions should have, which involves mathematical modeling and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions using a robotic arm, which involves computer vision techniques and falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
